name: 2-Methoxyethanol
Reason: 2-Methoxyethanol is a derivative of ethanol, which has a melting point of -114.1 degrees Celsius. The addition of a methoxy group (–OCH3) increases the molecular weight and volume, which might minutely raise the melting point. However, the presence of an ether linkage (–O–) has a slight lowering effect because it does not participate in hydrogen bonding as intensely as a hydroxyl group would. The net effect of the methoxy group and ether linkage is estimated to be a slight increase in the melting point, around 5 degrees Celsius.
